        <body xml:id="relations">
            <head>Relations</head>
            <p>Relations can be listed in all entities in a specific <gi>listRelation</gi>. This
                will contain <gi>relation</gi> elements with <att>name</att> taken from a list of
                values in the schema and can be updated.</p>
            <p>
                <gi>listRelation</gi> is allowed everywhere.</p>
            <p>For example, in a manuscript record within a <gi>msItem</gi> such relations and a
                description of them should be given within the element <gi>filiation</gi>
            </p>
            <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                <filiation>
                    <listRelation>
                        <relation name="saws:isDirectCopyOf" active="FSUffhludolfII21"
                            passive="BNFet1">
                            <desc>This manuscript is a direct copy of <ref type="mss"
                                    corresp="BNFet1"/>.</desc>
                        </relation>
                    </listRelation>
                </filiation>
            </egXML>
            <p>These relations can be much more precise than a simple list of <gi>ref</gi> elements
                stating similarity, and this is therefore the recommended way to encode similar
                manuscripts. Multiple relations can be stated if needed, for example if a manuscript
                A is a copy from two different manuscripts B and C of which one is certainly a
                translation from a Coptic manuscript D: one might have a relation between A and B, A
                and C, C and D or parts of them.</p>
            <p>In the <att>active</att> and <att>passive</att> attributes, please don't use # as
                this hinders the possibility to use further specific IDs within the record, and to
                point to a specific msItem, e.g.</p>
            <p>It is preferable to have a separate <gi>relation</gi> for each relationship, even if
                the same relation exists between one and several more items: <egXML
                    xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <relation name="snap:FatherOf" active="PRS11029Arkala"
                        passive="PRS11031WalattaM"/>
                    <relation name="snap:FatherOf" active="PRS11029Arkala" passive="PRS11032EsetaM"
                    />
                </egXML>
            </p>

            <p>Note that there is a specific <gi>relation</gi> to link BM and the Dillmann lexicon;
                the complete URL should be provided for the lemma ID, as in the <ref
                    target="LOC7011Meskwa" type="bm">sample file</ref>: <egXML
                    xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                    <relation name="betmas:hasLexiconEntry" active="LOC7011Meskwa"
                        passive="http://betamasaheft.eu/Dillmann/lemma/L65ae0746b7f9428da90682226ae6cc75"
                    />
                </egXML></p>
            <p>The following are some frequently used relation names, but there are many more
                readily available from the schema (see <gi>relation</gi>) and you can use others
                which are in the <ref target="ontologyView">ontology</ref>. In the <gi>relation</gi>
                page, as well as in your preferred editor, you will find in the schema a link to the
                actual concept and to a search for instances of that property in the project
                website.</p>
            <p>Before using one of these relations, please make sure you are aligned to others
                encoder usage. Below we provide some examples, and some more specific cases are
                detailed elsewhere, like the one above, but for many other values we have not done
                that yet. Open an issue, we will then agree on a way to proceed and update also this
                page.</p>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>mss-mss</head>
                <p><code>saws:isDirectCopyOf</code> is used as in the example below to state that a
                    manuscript is a direct copy of another manuscript <egXML
                        xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <relation name="saws:isDirectCopyOf" active="FSUffhludolfII21"
                            passive="BNFet1">
                            <desc>This manuscript is a direct copy of <ref type="mss"
                                    corresp="BNFet1"/>.</desc>
                        </relation>
                    </egXML>
                   </p>
                <p>The <ref target="http://www.ancientwisdoms.ac.uk/method/ontology/">SAWS ontology</ref> defines classes and properties to 
                    describe the relations between manuscripts (families, etc.) very deeply, but we do not have any example of this being used. If you would like to venture into this, it would be very interesting
                    so you are more than welcome! We will then add the examples here.</p>
           <!--     <p><code>saws:isAncestorOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>-->
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>mss-work</head>
                <p>
                    Most of the many relations between a manuscript and the abstract records identifying its contents are extracted directly from the semantics of the TEI encoding. If you feel the need to add such a relation
                    explicitly, open an issue to discuss the case, please.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>work-work</head>
                <p><code>saws:formsPartOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:isVersionInAnotherLanguageOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:contains</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>ecrm:CLP46i_may_form_part_of</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:isDifferentTo</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:isShorterVersionOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:isRelatedTo</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:follows</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>work-person</head>
                <p><code>saws:isAttributedToAuthor</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>ecrm:P129_is_about</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>dcterms:creator</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>person-person</head>
                <p><code>betmas:wifeOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>betmas:husbandOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>snap:AllianceWith</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>betmas:ordainedBy</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>rel:enemyOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>snap:SonOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>snap:FatherOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>person-mss</head>
                <p><code>saws:isCopierOf</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:hasOwned</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>lawd:hasAttestation</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> </egXML>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>person-work</head>
                <p><code>ecrm:P129i_is_subject_of</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> 
                        <relation name="ecrm:P129i_is_subject_of" active="PRS11855Diyosqoros" passive="LIT2375Synaxa">
                            <desc>Commemorated
                                on 3 Maskaram</desc>
                        </relation>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>dcterms:creator</code> a relation in this form is equivalent to say that this person is the author of the work
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> 
                        <relation  name="dcterms:creator" active="PRS12817Anestasyos" passive="LIT5809OntheBurial"/>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>betmas:isAuthorOfEthiopicTranslation</code> a relation in this form is equivalent to say that this person is the author of the Ethiopic translation of this work
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> 
                        <relation name="betmas:isAuthorOfEthiopicTranslation" active="PRS9187TaklaMa" passive="LIT2064Naydaq"/>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>saws:isAttributedAuthorOf</code> a relation in this form states that this person is an attributed author of this work. It would be nice to have some more details about this attribution when possible, for example, the source of the attribution.
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples"> 
                        <relation name="saws:isAttributedAuthorOf" active="PRS8746Semon" passive="LIT5334MiracleFurnishings"/>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>place-place</head>
                <p><code>gn:locatedIn</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <relation name="gn:locatedIn" active="LOC6577WestGondar" passive="LOC1426Amhara">
                            <desc>The West Gondar Zone is located in the ʾAmharā kǝllǝl.</desc>
                        </relation>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>gn:nearBy</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <relation name="gn:nearBy" active="LOC6564MaryamS" passive="LOC1311AksumS">
                            <desc>The new church of Māryām Ṣǝyon was built next to the old church of ʾAksum Ṣǝyon.</desc>
                        </relation>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
                <p><code>dc:relation</code> can be used to state a generic relation between two places
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <relation  name="dc:relation" active="LOC3577Gondar" passive="LOC6552Amhara">
                            <desc>Gondar was the capital of the Governo dell'Amhara during the Italian occupation.</desc>
                        </relation>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="level2">
                <head>person-place</head>
                <p><code>syriaca:has-relation-to-place</code>
                    <egXML xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/Examples">
                        <relation name="syriaca:has-relation-to-place" active="PRS4015Fasilada" passive="LOC3589Gorgor">
                            <desc>Fāsiladas ordered the burning of the library of the Jesuits' mission in
                                Gorgorā</desc>
                        </relation>
                    </egXML>
                </p>
            </div>

        </body>
